With the current `std::string` parameters, call sites that already build a temporary string can move it into the stored member; with `std::string_view`, that temporary still has to be built, then copied again into the member.
And for the short literal thread names, SSO likely makes any allocation concern moot anyway.

Okay I guess `BlockFilter::BuildParams()` already shows some precedent for a local `switch` based upon type. My suggestion still seems to be more in the spirit of the code around `g_filter_types`, but it's not a blocker.

